{"id":279,"date":"2020-10-12T14:11:03","date_gmt":"2020-10-12T12:11:03","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/xanasoft.com\/?page_id=279"},"modified":"2023-04-29T07:37:52","modified_gmt":"2023-04-29T07:37:52","slug":"filemigrationsettings","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/sandboxie-plus.com\/sandboxie\/filemigrationsettings\/","title":{"rendered":"File Migration Settings"},"content":{"rendered":"<h1>File Migration Settings<\/h1>\n<p><a href=\"SandboxieControl\">Sandboxie Control<\/a> &gt; <a href=\"SandboxSettings\">Sandbox Settings<\/a> &gt; File Migration:<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"http:\/\/sandboxie-plus.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/2\/2021\/03\/FileMigrationSettings.png\" alt=\"\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Before a sandboxed program can make changes to a file that already exists in your computer, Sandboxie first must make a copy of this file in the sandbox. However, making copies of very large files would be a long operation. For this reason, Sandboxie will only make copies of files that are below a certain maximum size. Files larger than this size will be considered read-only inside the sandbox, and any attempt to modify them will result in message <a href=\"SBIE2102\">SBIE2102<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>Use this settings page to set the maximum size threshold, and whether or not you wish to see message <a href=\"SBIE2102\">SBIE2102<\/a> issued when an attempt is made to modify files larger than that maximum size.<\/p>\n<p>Related <a href=\"SandboxieIni\">Sandboxie Ini<\/a> settings: <a href=\"CopyLimitKb\">CopyLimitKb<\/a>, <a href=\"CopyLimitSilent\">CopyLimitSilent<\/a>.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>File Migration Settings Sandboxie Control &gt; Sandbox Settings &gt; File Migration: Before a sandboxed program can make changes to a file that already exists in your computer, Sandboxie first must make a copy of this file in the sandbox. However, making copies of very large files would be a long operation. For this reason, Sandboxie &he